Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then cut it into 3 slices per person.
Place them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

== Vegetables ==

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto a #board{}. Cut into 2cm chunks.

Halve the @pomegranate{1}. Remove the seeds from the white pith by patting
the outside of the pomegranate with the back of a #spoon{}. Separate the
seeds and place into a #bowl{}. Careful - the juice stains. Discard the pith.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Drain the @sweetcorn{160%g} in a sieve.

== Spiced Corn Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the
heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn
to pick up some nice colour.

When the corn is charred, reduce the heat to medium-high. Stir in the garlic
and the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @water{50%ml} for the sauce into the frying pan. Stir in the
@vegetable stock paste{15%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and @sugar{1%tsp}.
Bring to the boil, then simmer for ~{1%minute}.

When the rice is cooked, add the corn and sauce to the #rice pan{}. Add the
@butter{20%g}, lime zest and squeeze in half the lime juice.

Stir well to combine, then taste and add more salt and pepper if needed. Cover
with a lid to keep warm.

== Halloumi ==

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined
with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle
of oil. Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each
side.

Once golden, remove the pan from the heat and allow to cool slightly.

Drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and remaining lime juice. Turn the halloumi to
glaze it.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, share the spiced rice and veg between your bowls.

Top with the glazed halloumi, avocado chunks and a good dollop of
@Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Sprinkle over the pomegranate seeds to
finish.

Enjoy!